3.01	Charles_Nicholson_(flautist)	Charles Nicholson (flautist)	Charles Nicholson (1795â€“1837), was a Liverpool-born flautist and composer, who performed regularly in London. He was soloist at many of the Philharmonic Society Concerts from 1816-1836, and first flautist with the principal theater orchestras. He toured extensively in Britain, but never on the Continent. Besides giving classes to many students, he wrote tutors for flute-playing which were published throughout the 19th century.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Charles_Nicholson00.jpg/220px-Charles_Nicholson00.jpg
